<HEAD>Koch To Host Presidential Candidates on TV</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Most of the presidential candidates have agreed
to take part in a New York primary eve question-and-answer
televised session with Mayor Edward I. Koch.
   The mayor announced Wednesday that he had lined up the
candidates, except for Republican Vice President George Bush, to
appear on the special program on April 18, at 11 p.m. on WNYW-TV.
