<HEAD>Poll Shows Party Voters Leaned To Bush, Dukakis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nebraska Republicans questioned in a recent
survey said they favored George Bush as their party's presidential
nominee, while Nebraska Democrats said they favored Michael Dukakis
as their nominee, according to the Omaha World-Herald.
   Forty-five percent of 347 registered Republicans surveyed in the
telephone poll last Thursday and Friday said they would vote for
