said. Six percent backed Sen. Albert Gore of Tennessee and 28
percent refused to answer or said they were undecided, the
newspaper said.
   SRI Research Center Inc., a subsidiary of Selection Research
Inc., conducted the random survey of selected registered voters for
the World-Herald.
   The poll had a margin of error of plus or minus 5.1 percentage
points for the Republican primary and 5.5 percentage points for the
Democrats, the newspaper said.
