<HEAD>Cameroon President Seeks Second Term</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YAOUNDE, Cameroon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Paul Biya will seek a second
five-year term, the ruling Democratic People's Assembly said in a
communique.
   Biya was elected to his first term in 1984 and is unchallenged
in the election set for April 24. His candidacy was announced
Wednesday.
   The ruling party is the only legal party in Cameroon, but the
country's constitution allows candidates to run independently if
they can produce petitions with at least 500 signatures of National
Assembly members, municipal counselers and chiefs.
