<HEAD>7-Year-old Child Sacrificed in Religious Ritual, Papers Say</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Contents of following may be offensive to some readers.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Hindu occult priest strangled a
7-year-old girl to offer her blood to a goddess in a ritual and
stored her body in his temple complex, it was reported Thursday.
   The priest, Narayan Gangadhar Poojary, and four others were
arrested after residents of Manpada village in the central Indian
Maharashtra state complained of a foul smell and called police, the
Hindustan Times and Patriot newspapers said.
   Police Inspector R.M. Patil said the body of the girl,
identified as Nandita Shinde, was found in the loft of a building
near the temple. It was hidden in fodder and cow dung.
   Police said the priest apparently called the girl inside the
temple Friday, the newspapers said. He was believed to have
strangled her and cut an artery in her left leg to draw blood for
the ritual offering aimed at pleasing a goddess, they said.
   Human sacrifices are outlawed in India, but still occur from
time to time, mainly in rural areas.
