<HEAD>East German Flees Homeland Over Fence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 20-year-old East German scaled a
10-foot fence under thick fog in northern Bavaria to escape his
communist homeland, West German police said Thursday.
   The escape took place Wednesday night in the Upper Franken
section of the region, according to Munich police. The man was not
identified.
   East German guards were seen searching the area after the escape
over the steel-mesh fence. They apparently were tipped off by
electronic sensors on the barriers, police said.
   At least 20 East Germans have fled over their homeland's
fortified barriers into West Germany this year.
