   Howard was later transferred to the Washington Hospital Center.
   A former schoolteacher and principal, Howard has been in
Congress since 1965.
   Howard has suffered two heart attacks during his more than two
decades in Congress. He was hospitalized for several days in 1984
in an episode doctors attributed to fatigue. He is a heavy
cigarette smoker.
   He has been chairman of the public works committee since 1981.
The panel considers multi-billion dollar highway and water projects
