<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Aliens-Fruit Bars,0152</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fifty-One Aliens Held for Deportation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COMMERCE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fifty-one illegal aliens smuggled into
the country from Mexico to sell frozen fruit bars and ice cream
from pushcarts were arrested and held for deportation Wednesday,
authorities said.
   The aliens, most of whom told authorities they had been brought
into the country in the last eight to 10 days, were sleeping on the
floor of the warehouse where the carts and products were stored,
said Ron Rogers, spokesman for the Immigration and Naturalization
Service.
   ``There were beer cans scattered all over the place, and pillows
and blankets on the floor,'' Rogers said. He said the men told
authorities they had been recruited in Mexico as street vendors.
   The operators of the vending company were being sought, he said.
   The aliens, one a teen-age boy and the rest adult males, were
being held for deportation hearings, he said.
</TEXT>
