<HEAD>Quotes From Presidential Candidates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Thursday by candidates
for the presidency:
   
   RICHARD GEPHARDT, asked if he would drop out of the presidential
race if he loses Michigan: ``No. I'm running for president and I'm
doing very well here in Michigan. .... My mother always told me to
cross one bridge at a time. That's what I'm trying to do.''
   
   PAUL SIMON, speculating he will pick up supporters if Gephardt
withdraws: ``There's no question there are some union leaders who
are now supporting Dick Gephardt who would find Paul Simon the most
attractive of the alternatives.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, calling for an increase in the minimum wage:
``I don't see how you can support a family on $3.35 an hour.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, saying a top priority as president would be to
stop drugs: ``As president, I will meet with the heads of state
where drugs are grown ... and stop the flow of drugs. Our borders
are exposed to the No. 1 killer of our people.''
   
   ALBERT GORE, saying he would have no problem in giving details
of more than $1 million in loans taken out by his campaign:
``There's nothing that is in any violation of any laws or
regulations and there's no cause for suggesting that there is.''
