bureaucratic deadbeats.
   ``Small businesses cannot afford to carry any customer for an
indefinite period of time, even if it is the U.S. government,''
Joseph A. Schaedel of the National Federation of Independent
Business told a House hearing Wednesday.
   An August 1986 report by the General Accounting Office estimated
that 24 percent of all federal agency bills were unpaid for more
than 30 days.
</TEXT>
