made millions trading on inside information, would earn a maximum
of 44 cents an hour at tasks ranging from landscaping to milking
cows if he's placed in the prison his sentencing judge has
recommended.
   Boesky likely will fulfill his three-year term at the Lompoc,
Calif., prison camp, a 700-man minimum security facility about 150
miles northwest of Los Angeles near the Pacific coast.
   A federal official said Wednesday that Boesky already had been
placed in a U.S. marshal's custody.
</TEXT>
