<1ST_LINE>r f PM-CNN-Telemundo     03-24 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-CNN-Telemundo,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>CNN To Produce Spanish-Language News Programming For Telemundo
Network</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cable News Network will produce Spanish-language
news programming for broadcast exclusively on the television
network operated by Telemundo Group Inc., company officials have
announced.
   The programming, slated to begin by May 31, will include a
30-minute national and international newscast, an hourlong
week-in-review program, and news briefs to appear five times daily,
Monday through Friday.
   The newscasts' correspondents will be based in New York,
Washington D.C., Miami, Los Angeles and key cities in Latin
America, the network said Wednesday.
   Telemundo Group, based in New York, owns and operates stations
in four of the five largest Hispanic markets in the United States _
Los Angeles, New York, Miami and San Francisco-San Jose _ and
reaches about 60 percent of U.S. Hispanic households.
   Telemundo also has affiliates in eleven other Hispanic markets.
</TEXT>
