<2ND_LINE>BC-Chevron Hires,0136</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chevron Corp. plans to add more than 1,500
workers by the end of the year, the largest annual increase in
staff since the oil company bought Gulf in 1984.
   The addition would include more than 300 workers in the San
Francisco Bay area, according to an article in an employee magazine.
   The company, the fourth-largest oil company in the nation, has
13,400 workers in the San Francisco area, including 2,748 at its
headquarters in San Francisco.
   Nearly half of the new employees will work in exploration. The
company will hire 400 workers to help find and produce oil in the
United States alone. In addition, 100 people will be involved in
exploration work in Canada and 160 will be hired for other nations.
</TEXT>
