<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WorldWheat     03-24 0118</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-World Wheat,0122</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>World Wheat Output Expected To Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   World ouptut of wheat is projected to rise in
1988, but could still fall short of demand for the second
consecutive year, the International Wheat Council said Thursday.
   In its first forecast of 1988 prospects, the council tentatively
put 1988 world output at 525 million metric tons _ 17 million above
last year's estimated total and 10 million below the 1986 record.
   Production of 525 million metric tons would fail to satisfy
projected demand for 1988, but current stocks could be used to make
up the shortfall, the council said.
   ``In the short- to medium-term, there should be no need for
great anxiety,'' it added.
</TEXT>
